If you use Zope, you can get the session this way:

    >>> from z3c.saconfig import named_scoped_session
    >>> Session = named_scoped_session('{{session_name}}')
    >>> session=Session()
    >>> session.add(Person(name='Donald Duck')) #assume we have a Person class
    
If you use the package standalone, do it this way:

    >>> from zope.configuration.xmlconfig import XMLConfig
    >>> import transaction
    >>> import {{packagename}}
    >>> XMLConfig('configure.zcml',{{packagename}})()
    
    assume we have a Person class in a module 'person'
    >>> from {{packagename}}.personal import Person 
    
    >>> from z3c.saconfig import named_scoped_session
    >>> Session = named_scoped_session('{{session_name}}')
    >>> session=Session()
    >>> session.add(Person(name='Donald Duck')) #assume we have a Person class
    
    >>> transaction.commit()
